qas.question: Which country consists of five administrative divisions?
As of 2016, there were how many districts in Tajikistan?
Each what is divided into one district?
As of 2016, there were how many jamoats in Tajikistan?

context: <b0_0>Tajikistan<b0_0/> consists of 4 administrative divisions. These are the provinces (viloyat) of Sughd and Khatlon, the autonomous province of Gorno-Badakhshan (abbreviated as GBAO), and the Region of Republican Subordination (RRP – Raiony Respublikanskogo Podchineniya in transliteration from Russian or NTJ – Ноҳияҳои тобеи ҷумҳурӣ in Tajik; formerly known as Karotegin Province). Each <b2_0>region<b2_0/> is divided into several districts, (Tajik: Ноҳия, nohiya or raion), which in turn are subdivided into jamoats (<b3_0>village-level self-governing units<b3_0/>) and then villages (qyshloqs). As of 2006[update], there were <b1_0>58<b1_0/> districts and <b4_0>367<b4_0/> jamoats in Tajikistan.
